<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="example.conference">
<body>

<metal:main fill-slot="main">
    <tal:main-macro metal:define-macro="main">

        <div tal:replace="structure provider:plone.abovecontenttitle" />

        <h1 class="documentFirstHeading" tal:content="view/label" />

        <div tal:replace="structure provider:plone.belowcontenttitle" />

        <p class="documentDescription" tal:content="context/description" />

        <div tal:replace="structure provider:plone.abovecontentbody" />
        <p>Here the table widget is set to DISPLAY_MODE in the
            updateWidgets method. The table cannot insert / delete or 
            auto-append. However, the individual cells are still in the
            default mode. They were created before the updateWidgets method was
            called. You must set the subform widgets to readonly also
            if you want to disable changes to the table.
        </p>

        <div id="content-core">
            <metal:block use-macro="context/@@ploneform-macros/titlelessform" />
        </div>

        <h2>Links</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-simple-edit-form"> demo-simple-edit-form </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-no-row-manipulators"> demo-edit-form-no-row-manipulators </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-no-auto-append"> demo-edit-form-no-auto-append </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-no-country"> demo-edit-form-no-country [not working]</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-column-widths"> demo-edit-form-column-widths </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-hidden-column"> demo-edit-form-hidden-column </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-read-only"> table is read-only, cells editable </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="@@demo-edit-form-read-only2"> table and cells are read-only </a>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <div tal:replace="structure provider:plone.belowcontentbody" />

    </tal:main-macro>
</metal:main>

</body>
</html>

